defaultoverriding 
defaultgoal was 
defaultto defeat terrorism and 
default&#xa0;
default“use every tool available to disrupt, dismantle, and destroy their capacity to conduct acts of terror. The final element to the Defeat goal is an aggressive, offensive strategy to eliminate capabilities that allow terrorists to exist and operate - attacking their sanctuaries; leadership; command, control, and communications; material support; and finances”.
default  
default&#xa0;
defaultAfter much debate, we concluded
default on the other hand
default that
default whilst sharing that absolute determination to protect
default the public, for the UK the
default appropriate strategy should start from denying the terrori
defaultsts that which they most sought, namely the creation of conditions of insecurity and fear amongst the public.  The strategic aim of CONTEST 
default– to reduce the risk in order to be able to maintain normality - 
defaulthas remained 
defaultconstant
default since then
default,
default 
defaultfrom its acceptance as gove
defaultrnment strategy in 2003 to date
default. Formally: 
default&#xa0;
default“The aim of CONTEST is to reduce the risk to the UK and its interests overseas from terrorism, so that people can go about their lives freely and with confidence.”
default&#xa0;
defaultThe caveats 
default‘freely’ and ‘with confidence’ 
defaultthat we added 
defaultare, however, 
defaultvery important 
defaultespecially 
defaultwhen it comes to the Pursue strand.
default  
default&#xa0;
defaultBy 
default‘
defaultfreely
default’
default should mean
default without having to sacrifice the values and liberties of a free democratic society. 
default 
defaultFurther tuning of counter-terrorism powers in the light of experience and of shifts in the modus operandi of terrorist groups must be expected, such as has already happened with TPIMS, 
defaultstop and search powers and reducing the length of time for which people can be held before charge for terrorist offences to 14 days.  But further 
defaultchanges 
defaultshould be at the margins, since the fundamental approach to 
defaultUK 
defaultCT legislation is sound in relation to the likely 
defaulttrajectory of the threat over the next few years.
default  Improved miniaturisation and reliability of the relevant technologies may, however, make it 
defaulteasier
default remotely to monitor the whereabouts 
defaultand communications 
defaultof 
defaulttagged convicted terrorist 
defaultoffenders 
defaultreleased 
defaulton licence in the community
default, an issue that will increase in salience as more of those guilty of terrorism related offences come to the end of their terms of imprisonment.  
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe caveat ‘with confidence’
default is also important.
default 
defaultWe can see the nation enjoying national security when there is maintenance of trust in the ability of the authorities to enable normal life to continue, 
defaultthat is, with 
defaultan absence of fear of attack, with 
defaultmarkets stable, inward investment
default flourishing
default, international travel safeguarded, overseas visitors a
defaultrriving and welcomed and so on.
