default and as 
defaultal-
defaultShaba
defaultab
default threatens in
default Somalia.  
defaultThe 
defaultAQ 
defaultprinter cartridge plot 
defaultout of Yemen 
defaultuncovered at Luton airport showed how terrorists far afield can threaten our security.
default  It must also be remembered that an increased threat of individual acts of violence increases the 
defaultdifficulty of the 
defaultdemands on the intelligence and security services to forestall attacks whilst still avoiding oppressive and counter-productive surveillance of the community
default as a whole
default.  And as the aftermath of the Woolwich murder showed the authorities also need to be able to stifle provocations from the extreme right that could threaten to undermine harmony in our town and cities.. 
default&#xa0;
defaultSuch developments in the terrorist threat will intensify the tension between nations that unilaterally defend their interests with military means - including by targeted killing and in 
defaultfuture by offensive use of 
defaultcyberspace – and those who seek collective security
default under international human
default rights 
defaultlaw
default.  A current example is the use of international humanitarian law to justify 
defaultlethal 
defaultUS armed 
defaultUAV
default attacks 
defaultoutside a recognised battle-space 
defaulton those regarded by their past 
defaultor current 
defaulthostile 
defaultterrorist activity
default as having foregone their non-combatant immunity.  Other nations such as the UK will be seeking to defend themselves within the different legal construct of international human rights law, authorising lethal force only when hostile intent is actually being shown. We will see more examples of overlapping legal regimes operating in a single geographical space as nations try to protect their interests against terrorist and criminal movements in ungoverned spaces overseas. 
defaultThe Committee will, I am sure, consider the ethically ambiguous position of the British public
default that has
default benefitted in that respect from the US armed UAV 
defaultprogramme 
defaultthat has removed several leading ter
defaultro
defaultrists who had been associated with plans to attack the UK and UK interests, measures that would not 
defaultlegally 
defaultbe permitted to the UK
default under the 
defaultoverseas part of the 
defaultPursue strategy
default.
default&#xa0;
defaultTerrorists will also adapt 
defaulttheir methods 
defaultto minimise the risk of failure
default.  In
default the future the biggest change in the conflict environment may well be in cyberspace
default,
default given our increasing dependence on cyber systems and the connectivity provided already by 8 billion users of mobile devices
default,
default and this may 
defaultmake it more likely that 
defaultviolence
default is expressed against us 
defaultfrom a safe distance lowering the risks to the attackers and lowering their threshold of violence.
default&#xa0;
defaultApplying the principle of 
defaultsubsidiarity
default, security issues that can be handled locally should be: there is no need for the concept of national security to become unnecessarily centralised. 
default 
defaultPersonal security, in the sense of absence of fear in one’s home or workplace or when travelling, has traditionally been seen as a matter for local police services.  
defaultThese services, for example, play an important part in everyday preventive policing 
defaultrelevant to the success of both
default the Pursue and 
defaultthe Prevent stra
defaultnds,
default something that needs to be recognised by the new Policing and Crime Commissioners
default at a time when policing resources are under huge strain
default.  
default&#xa0;
defaultEspecially since 9/11
default, however, it has become increasingly clear that important aspects of personal security are now national policy issues, because they have international roots in the activities of terrorists
default that see themselves as sharing a global religious ideology.
default 
default  T
defaulthere is 
defaultthus 
defaulta continuing need for a 
defaultstrong 
defaultnational counter-terrorism strategy to direct and align efforts supported by effective 
defaultnational 
defaultintelligence and police capability
default working in harmony.
default  The recent transfer of policy responsibility for the subject of serious and organised crime within the Home Office to OSCT to sit alongside counter-terrorism policy is prudent, given that we may see increasing overlap, or at least links, between criminal and terrorist gangs and that will include issues such as countering terrorist financing and terrorist access to cyber hacking capabilities.
default  
defaultOne consequence of the spread of cyber attack capabilities is that no longer can the 
defaultinternational community impose sanctions (such as the UN sanctions on Iran) and not expect the nation concerned to fight back with cyber means either directly or by proxies.  Another is that commercial companies overseas will find themselves the subject of cyber 
defaultor other form of 
defaultattack (for example after an environmental disaster or simply because they represent Western 
default‘Crusader’ 
defaultcapitalism).  It will be important that OSCT, with the agencies involved, look
defaults
default broadly at how such hostile long term developments can be countered under a future Pursue strategy.
default&#xa0;
defaultDoes that also argue for transferring the responsibility for police leadership in counter-terrorism from the Metropolitan Police Service (the Met) to the National Crime Agency
default (NCA)
default?  
defaultOne of the great successes of the last decade for the UK has been the partnership between the police service and the intelligence and security community
default, and their relationship with the Crown Prosecution Service, something 
defaultwith which that most nations struggle
default.  This 
defaultfortunate position 
defaultrests on established relations of trust between 
defaultdifferent 
defaultorganisations that have, rightly, different powers
default,
default mandates
default and cultures
default.  That cooperation has been successfully tested in circumstances of terrorist attack and attempted attack
default, and in the successful conviction of terrorists in the Courts
default.  Of course, the present arrangements involving the Security Service and the Met and the other police services in England and Wales and Scotland are not the only possible ones
default, nor necessarily
default the most economical.  But they have evolved under fire and I would be very cautious about seeking to replace them with a theoretical structure that might look tidier on paper, such as giving the lead to the NCA, until we have seen both a significant diminution in the thre
defaultat and 
defaultan NCA that has established itself firmly as being on the top of its game in relation to serious organised criminality. 
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultFurthermore, given the serious counter-terrorist effort still required in the UK, I would see great advantage in an all party statement from 
defaultthe Committee
default that the NCA 
defaultshould
default be given at least 5 years to bed down before the topic of counter-terrorism 
defaultresponsibility 
defaultis reconsidered.  What would erode unity of purpose and divert valuable nervous energy from the Pursue CT mission would be for officers on all sides to feel uncertain about the structure and their place in it over the next few years.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe purpose of Pursue is to stop terrorist attacks in this country and against our interest overseas. This means detecting and investigating threats at the earliest possible stage
default and 
defaultdisrupting terrorist activity before it can endanger the public and, wherever possible, prosecuting those responsible. 
default The key to Pursue therefore is pre-emptive intelligence, soundly assessed.
default&#xa0;
defaultSuch intelligence can come from three sources: 
defaultvolunteered from the community; accessed from intelligence sources, including traditional and new 
defaultsecret sources
default (such as social media intelligence)
default; and acquired from overseas liaisons.  Although intelligence oversight is the province of the Parliamentary Intelligence and Security Committee, the Home Affairs Committee may wish to reaffirm the importance of all three of the
defaultse
default avenues for accessing pre-emptive intelligence to allow terrorists to be identified, networks and attacks to be disrupted and those responsible for criminal acts brought to justice.  
default&#xa0;
defaultLooking ahead, it will be essential to an effective Pursuit campaign for the authorities to be able to continue to access and 
defaultanalyse
default 
defaultstored 
defaultcommunications meta-data and thus 
defaultuncover 
defaultthe communications of terrorist suspects and their 
defaultbackers and 
defaultfinanciers
default, even when these are hidden in the 
defaultvast global volumes of the 
defaultinternet.  Following the 
defaultcontroversy over revelations by
default Mr Snowden of details of the capabilities of the US and UK intelligence communities to achieve precisely that there is the danger that 
defaultwell-meaning but 
defaultexaggerated 
defaultconcerns over privacy
default, international information sharing
default 
defaultand the effectiveness of oversight will hinder 
defaultthe 
defaultfuture ability to track terrorists
default at home at abroad.  T
defaulthe Pursue effort
default would be seriously undermined by misguided efforts to rush in new European or national regulation
default or by failure by Parliament to keep up to date UK legislation on internet communications data
default.
default&#xa0;
defaultIt is likewise
default important to Pursue that the 
defaultdetailed 
defaultsources 
defaultand methods 
defaultof intelligence 
defaultwork 
defaultand 
defaultof 
defaultinvestigations 
defaultby police and Security Service do not become known to the terrorists themselves
default thus making their ambitions to harm us much easier to achieve
default.
default  The proceedings of relevant criminal and civil cases have already revealed much of how the security authorities operate, and 
defaultjudicial proceedings in this country 
default- civil as well as criminal - 
defaultmust be such as to be able to handle sensitive and secret material to 
defaultpre
defaultserve the interests of national security 
defaultwhilst dispensing
default justice.
default  
default&#xa0;
defaultThe spread of existing 
defaultand developing 
defaulttechnology will create dangers, for example with ever more sophisticated IEDs drawing on mobile phone and shaped charge technology, improvised communications networks being used by terrorists (as seen in the Mumbai attack), and improvised weapons systems where current conflicts already provide a reservoir of weapons, including surface to air missile systems as well as a training and hardening experience for British jihadists who are likely to seek to import their new skills into domestic ter
defaultr
defaultorism. The protection of UK and Western interests overseas
default,
default such as in aviation, oil and extractive industries
default,
default may well be
defaultcome
default more difficult, as was seen in the attack earlier this year by a 30 strong armed AQIM jihadist group on the BP/Statoil natural gas facility
default at
default 
defaultIn 
defaultAmenas
default 
defaultin south eastern Algeria
default near the Libyan border
