default&#xa0;
defaultAnother long term factor that should be considered when examining the future of the Pursue strand is that m
defaultost of the additional global population growth 
defaultthat 
defaultexperts predict
default 
defaultwill end up in the overcrowded urban littoral of developing 
defaultnations
default.  The capacity of these urban 
defaultmega-cities
default will be greatly exceeded in terms of security, governance, and basic utilities such as water and sanitation. In the 
defaultvast slums of 
defaultcoastal urban sprawl will hide terrorists, religious fanatics, and violent criminal and pirate gangs with international connections to the West
default including in the UK
default.  Safeguarding 
defaultUK and 
defaultWestern interests and citizens, and when necessary organising rescue and evacuation
default,
default is likely to be a preoccupation of military 
defaultand security 
defaultplanners.  
default&#xa0;
defaultWhat will be very different 
defaultin future 
defaultis that all of these many hundreds of millions of people living on the margin will nevertheless be electronically interconnected by their mobile devices
default,
default 
defaultexposed to ideologies hostile to us 
defaultand aware of global events as they happen.  The implications 
defaultfor counter-terrorism strategy and the Pursuit of ter
defaultr
defaultorists 
defaultwill be profound
default.
default 
default There should therefore be no let up in the 
defaultwork by HMG to co-operate
default with governments overseas and international organisations to improve global responses to terrorism at source whenever it appears.
default&#xa0;
defaultIt is the international dimension of our major security risks that drives the need for a redefinition of national security. 
defaultThe increased vulnerability of advanced cyber-networked societies and reliance upon complex just in time global l
defaultogistic networks and
default product sourcing widens the boundary of everyday security.   Interdependent markets, global travel patterns and labour migration interacting with transnational terrorism and piracy all 
defaultinternationalise
default domestic security concerns.  
defaultSuccess in counter-terrorism 
defaulttherefore 
defaultdepends on inte
defaultrnational collaboration
default including with countries whose legal outlook and respect for human rights differ from our own
default. 
default That should not stop us standing up for our values, whilst
default 
defaultencouraging and 
defaultsupporting 
defaultkey 
defaultpartners
default 
defaultto 
defaultbuild up 
defaulttheir capacity to investigate and prosecute terrorists overseas
default. 
